Gus Poyet believes it is a ‘disgrace’ that Premier League teams play twice in 48 hours between Christmas and New Year.

Sunderland were beaten 3-1 by Hull on Boxing Day and travel to Aston Villa on Sunday afternoon.

Poyet, though, has hit out at the festive fixture schedule.

