Patrick van Aanholt (shoulder) and Anthony Reveillere (calf) remain sidelined. 

The Black Cats failed to build on the euphoria of their Tyne-Wear derby win against Hull and their second-half performance was among their worst of the season.

And Poyet says the only consolation of the 48-hour turnaround is the chance to make amends for that poor showing.

‘One of the good things is that we play again in two days - that's the only good thing about it,’ he added.

‘We need to perform better. Better decisions on the ball, not hurry and get carried away with the noise and the fans pushing us forward.

‘We have some qualities and we need to respect those qualities. For us, it is important to believe in what we do and not what people think we should be doing.’

 

